[[File:DF9-NEGWT.png|thumb|right|250px|Golan Arms' DF.9 anti-infantry turret, commonly used by the Rebellion during the Galactic Civil War]] 
'''Anti-Infantry Turrets''', also known as '''anti-infantry batteries''',<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> and '''anti-personnel turrets''',<ref name="SoR">''[[Strongholds of Resistance]]''</ref> were ground-based [[Laser cannon/Legends|laser cannons]]. They employed precision [[Targeting computer/Legends|targeting computers]] to aim at enemy [[Infantry/Legends|infantry]] formations and support equipment. High-energy [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] bolts were then fired from the [[Cannon/Legends|cannons]], inflicting casualties and destroying materiel.<ref name="EGWT" />

==Models==
Several different models of Anti-Infantry Turret were in used during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. [[Taim & Bak/Legends|Taim & Bak]] manufactured the [[Bp.2 anti-infantry turret]], which was commonly used by the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="EaW">''[[Star Wars: Empire at War]]''</ref> [[Golan Arms/Legends|Golan Arms]] produced the [[DF.9/Legends|DF.9]], a turret famously used in the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] by the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], and the Twin DF.9, a more powerful, faster-firing model similar to the DF.9 but with two cannons.<ref name="EGWT" />

